<h1>Case 4 — City Info–Tourism Centre</h1>

<h2>Brief Description</h2>
<p>
The City Info–Tourism Centre acts as a smart tourist assistance hub, offering digital maps, 
personalized travel recommendations, real-time attraction details, and optimized city routes. 
It enhances the visitor experience by providing accurate and instant information.
</p>

<h2>Rising Problems</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Tourists getting lost or confused in an unfamiliar city layout.</li>
    <li>Overcrowding at popular attractions due to poor guidance.</li>
    <li>Slow access to attraction information and ticketing details.</li>
    <li>Inability to plan optimized travel routes across the city.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Solutions / Logic Used</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Hash Tables:</strong> For storing attraction data, timings, ratings, and nearby facilities.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority Queue (Heap):</strong> To rank attractions based on popularity, distance, and time.</li>
    <li><strong>Queue:</strong> Used for tourist help-desk management.</li>
    <li><strong>Dijkstra’s Algorithm:</strong> Generates shortest or personalized attraction routes.</li>
    <li><strong>Trie:</strong> Provides fast name-based search for attractions, hotels, restaurants, and guides.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Suitable SDGs</h2>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 8 — Decent Work & Economic Growth</strong>
    <p>Promotes tourism development and supports local businesses.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 11 — Sustainable Cities & Communities</strong>
    <p>Creates accessible, informational, and well-guided city experiences for tourists.</p>
</div>

<div class="sdg-box">
    <strong>SDG 9 — Industry, Innovation & Infrastructure</strong>
    <p>Encourages smart tourism infrastructure using digital technologies.</p>
</div>

